TY  - JOUR
T1  - Management Control of Blood Through a Short-Term Supply-Demand Forecast System
AU  - Frankfurter, George M.
AU  - Kendall, Kenneth E.
AU  - Pegels, C. Carl
Y1  - 1974/12/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.21.4.444
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.21.4.444
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 444
EP  - 452
VL  - 21
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Design, development, implementation and operation of a short-term blood inventory level forecast system is described. The primary purpose of the forecast system is to alert blood center management to the short-term inventory level of blood supplies so that they can take corrective notion to either reduce or increase blood collections. A test is performed on the system, and it is demonstrated that, management took action to reduce collections in response to higher than necessary inventory levels and increased collections during a period when insufficient inventory levels were forecast.
AB  - Design, development, implementation and operation of a short-term blood inventory level forecast system is described. The primary purpose of the forecast system is to alert blood center management to the short-term inventory level of blood supplies so that they can take corrective notion to either reduce or increase blood collections. A test is performed on the system, and it is demonstrated that, management took action to reduce collections in response to higher than necessary inventory levels and increased collections during a period when insufficient inventory levels were forecast.
